abstract: The Philippine president has renewed a threat to terminate an accord that allows American forces to train in the country unless Washington restored a visa of a political ally linked to human rights violations.
snippet: The Philippine president has renewed a threat to terminate an accord that allows American forces to train in the country unless Washington restored a visa of a political ally linked to human rights violations.
lead_paragraph: MANILA, Philippines — The Philippine president has renewed a threat to terminate an accord that allows American forces to train in the country unless Washington restored a visa of a political ally linked to human rights violations.
headline_main: Philippine Leader Threatens to End US Pact Over Ally's Visa
headline_print_headline: Philippine Leader Threatens to End US Pact Over Ally's Visa

abstract: As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
snippet: As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
lead_paragraph: OSAGE, Iowa — As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
headline_main: Democrats Struggle to Build Broad Support on Eve of Voting
headline_print_headline: Democrats Struggle to Build Broad Support on Eve of Voting

abstract: Alan Dershowitz was in line at Mar-a-Lago's lavish Christmas Eve buffet last month when President Donald Trump stopped to chat.
snippet: Alan Dershowitz was in line at Mar-a-Lago's lavish Christmas Eve buffet last month when President Donald Trump stopped to chat.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Alan Dershowitz was in line at Mar-a-Lago's lavish Christmas Eve buffet last month when President Donald Trump stopped to chat.
headline_main: Now on Trump's Team, Dershowitz Says,' I Haven't Changed'

abstract: His speech jolted the sleepy Senate to attention as he argued more explicitly than ever before for President Trump’s removal from office.
snippet: His speech jolted the sleepy Senate to attention as he argued more explicitly than ever before for President Trump’s removal from office.
lead_paragraph: Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the lead impeachment manager, stepped back to the Senate lectern around 10 p.m. Eastern to deliver one final argument for the day. It turned out to be a stemwinder, jolting the sleepy Senate to attention as Mr. Schiff argued more explicitly than ever before for President Trump’s removal from office.

headline_main: Impeachment Briefing: Day 2 of the Democrats’ Case

abstract: Four Americans were killed during the 2012 siege on the United States diplomatic mission and a C.I.A. annex.
snippet: Four Americans were killed during the 2012 siege on the United States diplomatic mission and a C.I.A. annex.
lead_paragraph: A Libyan militant was sentenced on Thursday to more than 19 years in prison by a federal judge for his role in the 2012 Benghazi attacks that killed four Americans, including the United States ambassador.

abstract: One took a seat in the visitors’ gallery perched above the chamber, and another emerged from a cloakroom with a magazine in hand.
snippet: One took a seat in the visitors’ gallery perched above the chamber, and another emerged from a cloakroom with a magazine in hand.
lead_paragraph: Senator Thom Tillis, Republican of North Carolina, wanted a change of perspective. So as the third day of President Trump’s impeachment trial stretched into yet another late night, he climbed a flight of stairs and took a seat in the Senate’s visitors’ gallery perched above the chamber.
